Claire Benard

Bio

Im a data scientist, keen to use data to solve problems that matter. My earlier work experience was in national and international charities and although Im now a consultant, I still volunteer for DataKind UK.

Blog

Most of my blogs talk about data in the charity sector, ethics and strategy.

6 things funders can do to support the responsible use of data | Impact on Urban Health (October, 21)

Using Data Beyond Monitoring & Evaluation | Data4good Fest (July, 21)

Three lessons I learned from a week in a tech start up | NCVO (March, 18)

Using R to produce innovative, quick and reproducible evidence | MERL Tech (March, 17)

Projects

Charity classifier | Check out the code
When registering with the Commission, charities must declare their sector of activity. This is a tick box with 16 options. Due to the nature of the sector, most organisations tick at least 2, and some as many as all 16 boxes. This work attempts to classify organisations based on the legal definition of their activity (their charitable object). Given the wording of their object, the model returns the most likely sector of activity.
